## algebra revisions needed

original formulas tested poorly on pre-emotional states:
  - Wonder ≠ Joy (no expectation to meet)
  - Overwhelm ≠ Sadness (nothing lost, just Input > Σ)

proposed additions:
```
Wonder = 含(novel) ∘ ⧖Ω          | hold new, defer binding
Overwhelm = Input > Σ            | saturation without loss
Ambivalence = Ω(A) ⇌ Ω(B)        | oscillating bindings
Identification = ¬Ω⁻¹(state)     | emotion unbinding refused → becomes identity
Loneliness = Σ(self) ∧ ¬∃(other) | capacity with nothing to fill it
```

